
Overview of noun volley

The noun volley has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (9) fusillade, salvo, volley, burst -- (rapid simultaneous discharge of firearms; "our fusillade from the left flank caught them by surprise")
2. (1) volley -- (a tennis return made by hitting the ball before it bounces)

Overview of verb volley

The verb volley has 5 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. volley -- (be dispersed in a volley; "gun shots volleyed at the attackers")
2. volley -- (hit before it touches the ground; "volley the tennis ball")
3. volley -- (discharge in, or as if in, a volley; "the attackers volleyed gunshots at the civilians")
4. volley -- (make a volley)
5. volley -- (utter rapidly; "volley a string of curses")
